From: rocm-polaris project
Subject: [PATCH] drm/amdkfd: skip PCIe atomics requirement for legacy GCN chips

KFD refuses to initialize compute queues on GCN 1.2 (gfx8) devices
when the platform does not support PCIe atomic operations. This blocks
ROCm/HIP compute on older platforms (pre-Haswell Intel, pre-Zen AMD).

GCN 1.2 GPUs handle atomics via their L2 cache without requiring
PCIe-level atomic support. The PCIe atomics check was a conservative
safety measure for system-wide multi-device coherency, which is not
required for single-GPU compute workloads.

This patch removes the PCIe atomics requirement for all legacy GCN
chips (the pre-IP-version ASIC path), enabling KFD compute on GCN 1.2
devices (Carrizo/gfx801, Tonga/gfx802, Fiji/Polaris/gfx803) on
platforms that lack PCIe atomic operations.

Signed-off-by: David Connolly <david@connol.ly>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdkfd/kfd_device.c | 3 ---
 1 file changed, 3 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdkfd/kfd_device.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdkfd/kfd_device.c
@@ -257,9 +257,6 @@
 		    asic_type != CHIP_TONGA)
 			kfd->device_info.supports_cwsr = true;

-		if (asic_type != CHIP_HAWAII && !vf)
-			kfd->device_info.needs_pci_atomics = true;
 	}
 }

